cast.text:
(1/3) 

Runners might feel this.

3 years ago I signed up for Berlin half marathon, prepped 3-4 weeks without any plan and ran 1:42. Nice!

Last year, I was like let‚Äôs make a plan then! (In fact my partner got the plan to be fair). 

So I got this 50 bucks pdf about how to prep to run a half in 1:30 within 12 weeks.

Berlin half is always beginning of April. 

I was super committed. Started training the first day of January and didn‚Äôt miss a session.

After a few sessions though I already realized it was actually too tough. 

Remember limping in the office and asking  how he dealt with the pain when he was training for the full marathons!? 
He said he usually didn‚Äôt have any pain, which should have gotten me thinking.

Well, I kept on pushing. 
Pushing too hard?

Three weeks before the race I got the flue and couldn‚Äôt even walk 30 meters without loosing my breath.

I fairly recovered, started at the race and barely made it to the end. 

All that work - no reward.
